# Mobile Responsiveness

RoleMule targets full mobile support down to 390px (iPhone 14). The viewport meta tag is set in `base.html`. Bootstrap 5 provides the grid and collapse utilities.

---

## Breakpoints Used

| Breakpoint | Width | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `xl` | `< 1200px` | Landing navbar collapses to hamburger |
| `lg` | `< 992px` | Dashboard navbar collapses to hamburger |
| `md` | `< 768px` | Primary mobile breakpoint — stack layouts, reduce padding |
| `sm` | `< 576px` | Auth card margins, small tweaks |
| `xs` | `< 480px` | Extra-small phones — font/padding reductions |

---

## Navbars

### Landing Page (`navbar_landing.html`)
Uses **`navbar-expand-xl`** — collapses at `< 1200px`.

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-xl navbar-dark fixed-top">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">...</a>
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button"
            data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav"
            aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false"
            aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
        <ul class="navbar-nav mx-auto">...</ul>
        <div class="nav-cta">...</div>
    </div>
</nav>
```

**Why `navbar-expand-xl`**: The landing nav has 6 links + 2 CTA buttons. At tablet widths (992–1199px) the items wrap to 2 lines without the xl breakpoint.

The hamburger icon uses a custom white SVG (Bootstrap's default is invisible on dark backgrounds):
```css
.navbar-toggler-icon {
    background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 30 30'%3e%3cpath stroke='rgba%28255%2C255%2C255%2C0.85%29' stroke-linecap='round' stroke-miterlimit='10' stroke-width='2' d='M4 7h22M4 15h22M4 23h22'/%3e%3c/svg%3e");
}
```

The collapsed menu gets a dark glass background **only on mobile** via:
```css
@media (max-width: 1199px) {
    .navbar-collapse {
        background: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.98);
        backdrop-filter: blur(24px);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        padding: 0.75rem 0 1rem 0;
        ...
    }
    .navbar-collapse .nav-cta {
        padding: 0 1rem;   /* ← padding on nav-cta, NOT negative margin on collapse */
    }
}
```

**Never use `margin: 0 -1rem` on `.navbar-collapse`** — it clips nav items at the left edge.

---

### Dashboard Home (`navbar_dashboard.html`)
Uses **`navbar-expand-lg`** — collapses at `< 992px`. The collapsed menu shows Help / Settings / Logout as full-width stacked buttons.

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="/dashboard">...</a>
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button"
            data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#dashboardNavMenu"
            aria-controls="dashboardNavMenu" aria-expanded="false"
            aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="dashboardNavMenu">
        <div class="user-info ms-auto">
            <a href="/help" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm nav-btn">...</a>
            <a href="/dashboard/settings" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm nav-btn">...</a>
            <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm nav-btn" data-action="logout">...</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</nav>
```

The inline `<style>` in `dashboard/index.html` handles the collapsed state — **no negative margin**:
```css
@media (max-width: 991px) {
    .navbar-collapse {
        background: var(--bg-card);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        padding: 1rem 0;          /* ← zero horizontal padding on the collapse panel */
    }
    .user-info {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: stretch;
        width: 100%;
        padding: 0 1rem;          /* ← horizontal spacing on child, not negative margin on collapse */
    }
    .user-info .nav-btn {
        width: 100%;
        justify-content: flex-start;
    }
}
```

### Sub-page Navbar (`navbar_subpage.html`)
Simple logo + "Back to Dashboard" link — no collapse needed. The back button text shrinks at `< 576px`.

