## Scrollable Tab/Pill Bars

Any horizontal tab or pill navigation must scroll on mobile instead of wrapping or overflowing. Apply this pattern to `.page-tabs`, `.settings-nav`, `.tools-nav`, `.nav-pills`, `.sub-tabs`, `.method-tabs`:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .my-tab-bar {
        overflow-x: auto;
        flex-wrap: nowrap;
        scrollbar-width: none;
        -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    }
    .my-tab-bar::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
    .my-tab-bar .tab-item { white-space: nowrap; }
}
```

The **application detail page** tabs hide their text labels on mobile (icons only) via:
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-tab span { display: none; }
}
```

