## Landing Page (`landing.css`) Breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Key changes |
|---|---|
| `max-width: 1199px` | Hero text centered, nav-cta stacks vertically, `code-preview` hidden |
| `max-width: 768px` | `agents-grid` / `features-grid` → 1-col, diagram stacks vertically |
| `max-width: 576px` | Hero title `2rem`, CTA buttons full-width, footer links wrap |
| `max-width: 480px` | Hero title `1.75rem`, pricing cards / CTA reduced padding |

---

## Non-Negotiables

1. **Never use `navbar-expand-lg` on the landing navbar** — it has too many items and wraps at tablet widths; always use `navbar-expand-xl`
2. **Never use `margin: 0 -Xrem` on `.navbar-collapse`** — clips nav item text; use `padding` on child elements instead
3. **Always add `scrollbar-width: none` + `::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none }`** when making a container `overflow-x: auto` — prevents an ugly scrollbar stub on desktop
4. **Toast and alert containers move to the bottom on mobile** — do not override `top` positioning in page-specific CSS without also overriding the mobile `bottom` rule in `app.css`
5. **`make build-frontend` instead of `npm run build` directly on macOS** — the Make target strips esbuild's quarantine flag first
